This paper is about evaluating dialogue systems using an adversarial loss, which is a common technique in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. The paper also discusses the use of RNNs, which are a type of neural network commonly used in ML, so cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely category. Additionally, the paper discusses the training and optimization of the model, which falls under cs.LG (Learning). The paper also discusses the practical issues of using this technique, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.SD (Software Engineering).
